\px[350] *A desk covered in maps and research. There's
\px[350] doodles and poems among the academic work.*
\px[320] *You find a bookmark hidden inside an eyeglass case.*
\px[500] "The Key to the sky:
\px[270] Mari's first 2 ID digits + his current favourite graphic novel"
\px[520] "The Key to fire:
\px[470] Noah's ID badge number"
\px[490] "The Key to the Gate:
\px[400] The usual: Professor's favourite book."
\px[300] "PS: Today feels like the end. Everyone's finally going to
\px[260] open the last chamber, but I don't feel like giving them the code.
\px[490] Not even the professor.
\px[230] "I'm desperate to erase my criminal records, but I can't help thinking:
\px[360] if we truly succeeded with the Chronoboros
\px[460] then why are we still here?
\px[290] "A paradox should have happened. I warned the professor
\px[390] about it but he kept brushing me aside.
\px[390] "But he'll see his blindless. They'll all see."
\px[450] "We're all wasting our time."

\px[400] *There's a plaque on the desk that reads
\px[360] "Prof. Boris Hardinger, PhD Anthropology".
\px[430] And a journal opened to a page:*
\px[350] "I believe we're extremely close to the Chronoboris."
\px[290] "I can tell because everyone is growing restless and desperate."
\px[300] "Of course the relic is expected to have this effect. After all,
\px[310] only the hungry grovel to the table. So too those who seek
\px[450] to reverse the hands of time."
\px[500] "I am no exception. \!
\px[480] I wish to see you terribly"
\px[390] "To get to the next room we must blast
\px[370] through the rubble with minimal explosives.
\px[250] "Since everyone is becoming increasingly distrustful of one another,
\px[230] I entrusted locked bags containing the explosive parts to two students,
\px[400] while the list of codes are with a third."
\px[250] "Additionally, I advised the students to set up their respective
\px[330] desks directly in front of their assigned quarters.
\px[350] "Note: my most favoured novel has not changed.
\px[250] I will put it in my room once the bookshelf gets moved into here."
